{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The humanitarian model has barely changed"},{"time":3000,"text":"since the early 20th century."},{"time":5000,"text":"Its origins are firmly rooted"},{"time":7000,"text":"in the analog age."},{"time":9000,"text":"And there is a major shift coming on the horizon."},{"time":13000,"text":"The catalyst for this change"},{"time":15000,"text":"was the major earthquake that struck Haiti"},{"time":18000,"text":"on the 12th of January in 2010."},{"time":22000,"text":"Haiti was a game changer."},{"time":25000,"text":"The earthquake destroyed the capital of Port-au-Prince,"},{"time":29000,"text":"claiming the lives of some 320,000 people,"},{"time":32000,"text":"rendering homeless"},{"time":34000,"text":"about 1.2 million people."},{"time":37000,"text":"Government institutions were completely decapitated,"},{"time":40000,"text":"including the presidential palace."},{"time":43000,"text":"I remember standing"},{"time":45000,"text":"on the roof of the Ministry of Justice"},{"time":47000,"text":"in downtown Port-au-Prince."},{"time":49000,"text":"It was about two meters high,"},{"time":51000,"text":"completely squashed"},{"time":53000,"text":"by the violence of the earthquake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"For those of us on the ground in those early days,"},{"time":58000,"text":"it was clear for even the most disaster-hardened veterans"},{"time":61000,"text":"that Haiti was something different."},{"time":63000,"text":"Haiti was something we hadn't seen before."},{"time":67000,"text":"But Haiti provided us with something else unprecedented."},{"time":70000,"text":"Haiti allowed us to glimpse into a future"},{"time":73000,"text":"of what disaster response might look like"},{"time":76000,"text":"in a hyper-connected world"},{"time":78000,"text":"where people have access"},{"time":80000,"text":"to mobile smart devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"Because out of the urban devastation"},{"time":85000,"text":"in Port-au-Prince"},{"time":87000,"text":"came a torrent of SMS texts --"},{"time":90000,"text":"people crying for help,"},{"time":92000,"text":"beseeching us for assistance,"},{"time":94000,"text":"sharing data, offering support,"},{"time":96000,"text":"looking for their loved ones."},{"time":98000,"text":"This was a situation"},{"time":100000,"text":"that traditional aid agencies had never before encountered."},{"time":103000,"text":"We were in one of the poorest countries on the planet,"},{"time":106000,"text":"but 80 percent of the people"},{"time":109000,"text":"had mobile devices in their hands."},{"time":111000,"text":"And we were unprepared for this,"},{"time":113000,"text":"and they were shaping the aid effort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"Outside Haiti also, things were looking different."},{"time":119000,"text":"Tens of thousands of so-called digital volunteers"},{"time":122000,"text":"were scouring the Internet,"},{"time":124000,"text":"converting tweets"},{"time":126000,"text":"that had already been converted from texts"},{"time":128000,"text":"and putting these into open-source maps,"},{"time":130000,"text":"layering them with all sorts of important information --"},{"time":133000,"text":"people like Crisis Mappers and Open Street Map --"},{"time":136000,"text":"and putting these on the Web for everybody --"},{"time":138000,"text":"the media, the aid organizations and the communities themselves --"},{"time":141000,"text":"to participate in and to use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"Back in Haiti,"},{"time":146000,"text":"people were increasingly turning"},{"time":148000,"text":"to the medium of SMS."},{"time":150000,"text":"People that were hungry and hurting"},{"time":152000,"text":"were signaling their distress,"},{"time":154000,"text":"were signaling their need for help."},{"time":157000,"text":"On street sides all over Port-au-Prince,"},{"time":160000,"text":"entrepreneurs sprung up"},{"time":162000,"text":"offering mobile phone charging stations."},{"time":165000,"text":"They understood more than we did"},{"time":167000,"text":"people's innate need"},{"time":169000,"text":"to be connected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"Never having been confronted"},{"time":173000,"text":"with this type of situation before,"},{"time":175000,"text":"we wanted to try and understand"},{"time":177000,"text":"how we could tap into this incredible resource,"},{"time":180000,"text":"how we could really leverage"},{"time":182000,"text":"this incredible use of mobile technology"},{"time":184000,"text":"and SMS technology."},{"time":186000,"text":"We started talking with a local telecom provider called Voil√†,"},{"time":190000,"text":"which is a subsidiary of Trilogy International."},{"time":194000,"text":"We had basically three requirements."},{"time":196000,"text":"We wanted to communicate"},{"time":198000,"text":"in a two-way form of communication."},{"time":200000,"text":"We didn't want to shout; we needed to listen as well."},{"time":203000,"text":"We wanted to be able to target"},{"time":205000,"text":"specific geographic communities."},{"time":207000,"text":"We didn't need to talk to the whole country at the same time."},{"time":210000,"text":"And we wanted it to be easy to use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"Out of this rubble of Haiti and from this devastation"},{"time":216000,"text":"came something that we call TERA --"},{"time":218000,"text":"the Trilogy Emergency Response Application --"},{"time":221000,"text":"which has been used to support the aid effort"},{"time":223000,"text":"ever since."},{"time":225000,"text":"It has been used to help communities prepare for disasters."},{"time":228000,"text":"It has been used to signal early warning"},{"time":231000,"text":"in advance of weather-related disasters."},{"time":233000,"text":"It's used for public health awareness campaigns"},{"time":236000,"text":"such as the prevention of cholera."},{"time":238000,"text":"And it is even used for sensitive issues"},{"time":241000,"text":"such as building awareness"},{"time":243000,"text":"around gender-based violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245000,"text":"But does it work?"},{"time":248000,"text":"We have just published"},{"time":250000,"text":"an evaluation of this program,"},{"time":253000,"text":"and the evidence that is there for all to see"},{"time":256000,"text":"is quite remarkable."},{"time":259000,"text":"Some 74 percent of people"},{"time":261000,"text":"received the data."},{"time":263000,"text":"Those who were intended to receive the data,"},{"time":265000,"text":"74 percent of them received it."},{"time":267000,"text":"96 percent of them"},{"time":269000,"text":"found it useful."},{"time":271000,"text":"83 percent of them took action --"},{"time":274000,"text":"evidence that it is indeed empowering."},{"time":276000,"text":"And 73 percent of them shared it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"The TERA system"},{"time":282000,"text":"was developed from Haiti"},{"time":284000,"text":"with support of engineers in the region."},{"time":287000,"text":"It is a user-appropriate technology"},{"time":289000,"text":"that has been used for humanitarian good to great effect."},{"time":292000,"text":"Technology is transformational."},{"time":295000,"text":"Right across the developing world,"},{"time":297000,"text":"citizens and communities"},{"time":299000,"text":"are using technology"},{"time":301000,"text":"to enable them to bring about change, positive change,"},{"time":303000,"text":"in their own communities."},{"time":305000,"text":"The grassroots has been strengthened"},{"time":307000,"text":"through the social power of sharing"},{"time":309000,"text":"and they are challenging the old models,"},{"time":311000,"text":"the old analog models"},{"time":313000,"text":"of control and command."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"One illustration of the transformational power of technology"},{"time":319000,"text":"is in Kibera."},{"time":321000,"text":"Kibera is one of Africa's largest slums."},{"time":323000,"text":"It's on the outskirts of Nairobi,"},{"time":325000,"text":"the capital city of Kenya."},{"time":327000,"text":"It's home to an unknown number of people --"},{"time":329000,"text":"some say between 250,000"},{"time":331000,"text":"and 1.2 million."},{"time":333000,"text":"If you were to arrive in Nairobi today"},{"time":335000,"text":"and pick up a tourist map,"},{"time":337000,"text":"Kibera is represented"},{"time":339000,"text":"as a lush, green national park"},{"time":341000,"text":"devoid of human settlement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"Young people living in Kibera"},{"time":345000,"text":"in their community,"},{"time":347000,"text":"with simple handheld devices,"},{"time":349000,"text":"GPS handheld devices and SMS-enabled mobile phones,"},{"time":353000,"text":"have literally put themselves on the map."},{"time":355000,"text":"They have collated crowd-sourced data"},{"time":357000,"text":"and rendered the invisible visible."},{"time":360000,"text":"People like Josh and Steve"},{"time":363000,"text":"are continuing to layer information upon information,"},{"time":366000,"text":"real-time information, Tweet it and text it onto these maps"},{"time":369000,"text":"for all to use."},{"time":371000,"text":"You can find out about the latest impromptu music session."},{"time":374000,"text":"You can find out about the latest security incident."},{"time":376000,"text":"You can find out about places of worship."},{"time":378000,"text":"You can find out about the health centers."},{"time":380000,"text":"You can feel the dynamism"},{"time":382000,"text":"of this living, breathing community."},{"time":384000,"text":"They also have their own news network on YouTube"},{"time":387000,"text":"with 36,000 viewers at the moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"They're showing us what can be done"},{"time":393000,"text":"with mobile, digital technologies."},{"time":395000,"text":"They're showing that the magic of technology"},{"time":397000,"text":"can bring the invisible visible."},{"time":399000,"text":"And they are giving a voice to themselves."},{"time":401000,"text":"They are telling their own story,"},{"time":404000,"text":"bypassing the official narrative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"And we're seeing from all points on the globe similar stories."},{"time":409000,"text":"In Mongolia for instance,"},{"time":411000,"text":"where 30 percent of the people are nomadic,"},{"time":413000,"text":"SMS information systems are being used"},{"time":416000,"text":"to track migration and weather patterns."},{"time":418000,"text":"SMS is even used"},{"time":420000,"text":"to hold herder summits"},{"time":422000,"text":"from remote participation."},{"time":424000,"text":"And if people are migrating"},{"time":426000,"text":"into urban, unfamiliar, concrete environments,"},{"time":428000,"text":"they can also be helped in anticipation"},{"time":430000,"text":"with social supporters ready and waiting for them"},{"time":433000,"text":"based on SMS knowledge."},{"time":435000,"text":"In Nigeria,"},{"time":437000,"text":"open-source SMS tools"},{"time":440000,"text":"are being used by the Red Cross community workers"},{"time":443000,"text":"to gather information from the local community"},{"time":446000,"text":"in an attempt to better understand and mitigate"},{"time":448000,"text":"the prevalence of malaria."},{"time":450000,"text":"My colleague, Jason Peat, who runs this program,"},{"time":453000,"text":"tells me it's 10 times faster and 10 times cheaper"},{"time":456000,"text":"than the traditional way of doing things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"And not only is it empowering to the communities,"},{"time":461000,"text":"but really importantly,"},{"time":463000,"text":"this information stays in the community"},{"time":465000,"text":"where it is needed to formulate long-term health polices."},{"time":469000,"text":"We are on a planet"},{"time":471000,"text":"of seven billion people,"},{"time":474000,"text":"five billion mobile subscriptions."},{"time":477000,"text":"By 2015,"},{"time":479000,"text":"there will be three billion smartphones in the world."},{"time":484000,"text":"The U.N. broadband commission"},{"time":486000,"text":"has recently set targets"},{"time":488000,"text":"to help broadband access"},{"time":490000,"text":"in 50 percent of the Developing World,"},{"time":493000,"text":"compared to 20 percent today."},{"time":495000,"text":"We are hurtling towards a hyper-connected world"},{"time":498000,"text":"where citizens from all cultures and all social strata"},{"time":501000,"text":"will have access to smart, fast mobile devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505000,"text":"People are understanding,"},{"time":507000,"text":"from Cairo to Oakland,"},{"time":509000,"text":"that there are new ways to come together,"},{"time":511000,"text":"there are new ways to mobilize,"},{"time":513000,"text":"there are new ways to influence."},{"time":517000,"text":"A transformation is coming which needs to be understood"},{"time":520000,"text":"by the humanitarian structures and humanitarian models."},{"time":523000,"text":"The collective voices of people"},{"time":525000,"text":"needs to be more integrated through new technologies"},{"time":528000,"text":"into the organizational strategies and plans of actions"},{"time":530000,"text":"and not just recycled"},{"time":532000,"text":"for fundraising or marketing."},{"time":534000,"text":"We need to, for example, embrace"},{"time":536000,"text":"the big data,"},{"time":538000,"text":"the knowledge that is there from market leaders"},{"time":540000,"text":"who understand what it means"},{"time":542000,"text":"to use and leverage big data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"One idea that I'd like you to consider, for instance,"},{"time":548000,"text":"is to take a look at our IT departments."},{"time":551000,"text":"They're normally backroom or basement hardware service providers,"},{"time":554000,"text":"but they need to be elevated to software strategists."},{"time":557000,"text":"We need people in our organizations"},{"time":559000,"text":"who know what it's like to work with big data."},{"time":561000,"text":"We need technology"},{"time":563000,"text":"as a core organizational principle."},{"time":565000,"text":"We need technological strategists in the boardroom"},{"time":568000,"text":"who can ask and answer the question,"},{"time":570000,"text":"\"What would Amazon or Google"},{"time":572000,"text":"do with all of this data?\""},{"time":574000,"text":"and convert it to humanitarian good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"The possibilities"},{"time":580000,"text":"that new digital technologies are bringing"},{"time":582000,"text":"can help humanitarian organizations,"},{"time":584000,"text":"not only ensure"},{"time":586000,"text":"that people's right to information is met,"},{"time":588000,"text":"or that they have their right to communicate,"},{"time":591000,"text":"but I think in the future,"},{"time":593000,"text":"humanitarian organizations will also have to anticipate"},{"time":596000,"text":"the right for people to access"},{"time":598000,"text":"critical communication technologies"},{"time":600000,"text":"in order to ensure"},{"time":602000,"text":"that their voices are heard,"},{"time":604000,"text":"that they're truly participating,"},{"time":606000,"text":"that they're truly empowered in the humanitarian world."},{"time":609000,"text":"It has always been the elusive ideal"},{"time":612000,"text":"to ensure full participation of people affected by disasters"},{"time":615000,"text":"in the humanitarian effort."},{"time":618000,"text":"We now have the tools. We now have the possibilities."},{"time":621000,"text":"There are no more reasons not to do it."},{"time":625000,"text":"I believe we need to bring the humanitarian world"},{"time":628000,"text":"from analog to digital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}